I’m a former carnie (almost 20yrs) and I’m just having a laugh on how your making the cotton candy from actual hard candies. I’ve spent my fair share making cotton candy (never experimented what you guys are doing) and I’ll tell ya you guys sure try your best at it.

How I make cotton candy. I would take a 50lb sack of pure cain sugar. fill sugar into a 22qt food grade round container with about a teaspoon of floss. blend well and pour a scoop into floss machine. turn on heater then motor and allow cotton candy to build up along the walls of the bowl. repeat filling floss into machine while on when needed. You should have a net lining the inside bowl to help catch the cotton candy and plus half of the melted sugar for easier clean up. I noticed no leather straps on the spindle head, it helps keep the mix from flying everywhere when pouring into machine while running (you’ll still get overspray but not the whole amount when pouring). adjust speed when floss starts to fluff up along the walls. Allow a generous amount of cotton candy to build up, stick cone into the inner section, twist and pull up at the same time. I would just grab twist & then stuff into bag. I usually have two floss machines running at the same time to mix flavors while packing.

I always enjoy watching your videos, but I do have a little criticism...
You're using the machine wrong; Before adding the sugar to the heating head and to prevent it going everywhere the power should be temporarily turned off (after preheating of course), the stick should be held as vertical as possible, almost touching the bottom of the pan, (exactly center of the heating head and pan wall), rotating the stick clockwise around the inside the pan, (revolving around the heating head)... You don't have to spin the stick, but in doing so will yield a more uniform cotton candy (fairy floss in Australia) on the stick.
Cheers.
